"{\"uid\": \"newstatesman.com-culture-sport-2024-07-the-paris-olympics-opening-ceremony-was-more-eurovision-than-bastille-day\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"Reviewing politicsand culture since 1913 Rainfall and narrative incoherence marred an ambitious international parade.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 118, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"politicsand culture\", \"from\": 10, \"to\": 29}, {\"ngram\": \"1913 Rainfall\", \"from\": 36, \"to\": 49}, {\"ngram\": \"narrative incoherence\", \"from\": 54, \"to\": 75}, {\"ngram\": \"an ambitious international parade\", \"from\": 83, \"to\": 116}]}, {\"sentence\": \"ByNicholas Harris The supremely frustrating part of visiting any city is transit: the gruelling, hot, bureaucratic business of getting from park to landmark to cathedral.\", \"from\": 120, \"to\": 291, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The supremely frustrating part\", \"from\": 138, \"to\": 168}, {\"ngram\": \"any city\", \"from\": 181, \"to\": 189}, {\"ngram\": \"transit\", \"from\": 193, \"to\": 200}, {\"ngram\": \"the gruelling, hot, bureaucratic business\", \"from\": 202, \"to\": 243}, {\"ngram\": \"park\", \"from\": 260, \"to\": 264}, {\"ngram\": \"cathedral\", \"from\": 280, \"to\": 289}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's the most boring and yet fortunately the most forgettable component of any holiday.\", \"from\": 292, \"to\": 379, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the most boring and yet fortunately the most forgettable component\", \"from\": 297, \"to\": 363}, {\"ngram\": \"any holiday\", \"from\": 367, \"to\": 378}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But, in a baffling turn for an event that is at least partially a tourism advert, it seems the ambition of the Paris Olympics opening ceremony was to try to recreate that experience and serve it up as televisual longform.\", \"from\": 380, \"to\": 601, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a baffling turn\", \"from\": 388, \"to\": 403}, {\"ngram\": \"an event\", \"from\": 408, \"to\": 416}, {\"ngram\": \"at least partially a tourism advert\", \"from\": 425, \"to\": 460}, {\"ngram\": \"the ambition\", \"from\": 471, \"to\": 483}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics opening ceremony\", \"from\": 487, \"to\": 522}, {\"ngram\": \"that experience\", \"from\": 546, \"to\": 561}, {\"ngram\": \"televisual longform\", \"from\": 581, \"to\": 600}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The overwhelming mood of the opening ceremony was tedium.\", \"from\": 602, \"to\": 659, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The overwhelming mood\", \"from\": 602, \"to\": 623}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 627, \"to\": 647}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And perhaps its one salvation was that, in its later stages, it featured enough madness to distract from the banality.\", \"from\": 660, \"to\": 778, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"its one salvation\", \"from\": 672, \"to\": 689}, {\"ngram\": \"its later stages\", \"from\": 703, \"to\": 719}, {\"ngram\": \"enough madness\", \"from\": 733, \"to\": 747}, {\"ngram\": \"the banality\", \"from\": 765, \"to\": 777}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ahead of yesterday evening's proceedings, the much-touted USP was itsen plein airquality.\", \"from\": 780, \"to\": 869, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"yesterday evening's proceedings\", \"from\": 789, \"to\": 820}, {\"ngram\": \"the much-touted USP\", \"from\": 822, \"to\": 841}, {\"ngram\": \"itsen plein airquality\", \"from\": 846, \"to\": 868}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That is, instead of being based in a single stadium like every previous opening ceremony, Paris's show would be arranged along a stretch of the River Seine.\", \"from\": 870, \"to\": 1026, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 960, \"end\": 965, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9654379747492232e-30, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1014, \"end\": 1025, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a single stadium\", \"from\": 905, \"to\": 921}, {\"ngram\": \"every previous opening ceremony\", \"from\": 927, \"to\": 958}, {\"ngram\": \"a stretch\", \"from\": 997, \"to\": 1006}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The key objectives were the same as ever: get the Olympic flame to the Olympic cauldron, and parade the competing athletes, all in such a way that keeps 1.5 billion viewers from nodding off.\", \"from\": 1027, \"to\": 1217, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The key objectives\", \"from\": 1027, \"to\": 1045}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic flame\", \"from\": 1073, \"to\": 1090}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic cauldron\", \"from\": 1094, \"to\": 1114}, {\"ngram\": \"the competing athletes\", \"from\": 1127, \"to\": 1149}, {\"ngram\": \"such a way\", \"from\": 1158, \"to\": 1168}, {\"ngram\": \"1.5 billion viewers\", \"from\": 1180, \"to\": 1199}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But, this being France, there had to be a metatextual boast of its structural innovation.\", \"from\": 1218, \"to\": 1307, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1234, \"end\": 1240, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999958899934, \"rank\": 3.470681353663993e-09, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a metatextual boast\", \"from\": 1258, \"to\": 1277}, {\"ngram\": \"its structural innovation\", \"from\": 1281, \"to\": 1306}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The story of the ceremony began with a video of the torch arriving incorrectly at an emptystade, before Zinedine Zidane turned up to whisk it off to its true destination.\", \"from\": 1308, \"to\": 1478, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1412, \"end\": 1427, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zinedine_Zidane\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Zinedine Zidane\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zinedine_Zidane\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zinedine_Zidane\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The story\", \"from\": 1308, \"to\": 1317}, {\"ngram\": \"the ceremony\", \"from\": 1321, \"to\": 1333}, {\"ngram\": \"a video\", \"from\": 1345, \"to\": 1352}, {\"ngram\": \"the torch\", \"from\": 1356, \"to\": 1365}, {\"ngram\": \"an emptystade\", \"from\": 1390, \"to\": 1403}, {\"ngram\": \"its true destination\", \"from\": 1457, \"to\": 1477}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He then passed the torch to a mysterious runner: a masked Frenchman in an 18th-century frock coat.\", \"from\": 1480, \"to\": 1578, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the torch\", \"from\": 1495, \"to\": 1504}, {\"ngram\": \"a mysterious runner\", \"from\": 1508, \"to\": 1527}, {\"ngram\": \"a masked Frenchman\", \"from\": 1529, \"to\": 1547}, {\"ngram\": \"an 18th-century frock coat\", \"from\": 1551, \"to\": 1577}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And from here it seemed the opening ceremony's premises were set.\", \"from\": 1579, \"to\": 1644, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony's premises\", \"from\": 1603, \"to\": 1634}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The flame would be parkoured to its final destination by the lost Assassin's Creed character over rooftop and chimney.\", \"from\": 1645, \"to\": 1763, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1711, \"end\": 1719, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Order_of_Assassins\", \"score\": 0.6765142961277042, \"rank\": 0.47816456759722437, \"text\": \"Assassin\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Order_of_Assassins\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Order_of_Assassins\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The flame\", \"from\": 1645, \"to\": 1654}, {\"ngram\": \"its final destination\", \"from\": 1677, \"to\": 1698}, {\"ngram\": \"rooftop\", \"from\": 1743, \"to\": 1750}, {\"ngram\": \"chimney\", \"from\": 1755, \"to\": 1762}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile the athletes themselves travelled in a fleet of boats downriver (most nations got their own boat, but some had to share).\", \"from\": 1764, \"to\": 1895, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 1774, \"to\": 1786}, {\"ngram\": \"a fleet\", \"from\": 1811, \"to\": 1818}, {\"ngram\": \"boats downriver\", \"from\": 1822, \"to\": 1837}, {\"ngram\": \"most nations\", \"from\": 1839, \"to\": 1851}, {\"ngram\": \"their own boat\", \"from\": 1856, \"to\": 1870}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But, for this evening, the Seine was not just any river.\", \"from\": 1896, \"to\": 1952, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1923, \"end\": 1928, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7723553842224774e-31, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this evening\", \"from\": 1905, \"to\": 1917}, {\"ngram\": \"just any river\", \"from\": 1937, \"to\": 1951}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Under the command of the French state, it became a miracle of fountains, showering the Olympians as they sailed by.\", \"from\": 1953, \"to\": 2068, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1978, \"end\": 1984, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9988095802803378, \"rank\": 0.0011887877534325609, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the command\", \"from\": 1959, \"to\": 1970}, {\"ngram\": \"a miracle\", \"from\": 2002, \"to\": 2011}, {\"ngram\": \"fountains\", \"from\": 2015, \"to\": 2024}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympians\", \"from\": 2036, \"to\": 2049}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Unfortunately for them, however, what was presumably planned as a decorative sprinkle soon became a deluge, as heavy rainfall swamped the city.\", \"from\": 2069, \"to\": 2212, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a decorative sprinkle\", \"from\": 2133, \"to\": 2154}, {\"ngram\": \"a deluge\", \"from\": 2167, \"to\": 2175}, {\"ngram\": \"heavy rainfall\", \"from\": 2180, \"to\": 2194}, {\"ngram\": \"the city\", \"from\": 2203, \"to\": 2211}]}, {\"sentence\": \"National pride briefly swept Britain as images from the sideline showed Keir Starmer in a proper coat, and not one of those awful transparent ponchos.\", \"from\": 2213, \"to\": 2363, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2213, \"end\": 2227, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patriotism\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"National pride\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patriotism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patriotism\"}, {\"begin\": 2242, \"end\": 2249, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999999871806723, \"rank\": 1.2544732054292375e-08, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 2285, \"end\": 2297, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keir_Starmer\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Keir Starmer\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keir_Starmer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keir_Starmer\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"images\", \"from\": 2253, \"to\": 2259}, {\"ngram\": \"the sideline\", \"from\": 2265, \"to\": 2277}, {\"ngram\": \"a proper coat\", \"from\": 2301, \"to\": 2314}, {\"ngram\": \"those awful transparent ponchos\", \"from\"